Product name: Creeping Thyme ground cover, 1000 seeds, fragrant herb, pink blooms, perennial zones 4 to 9, sun or light shade, deerproof, Thymus serpyllum
Description:
This miniature thyme is fragrant, pretty, and charming. It's also incredibly useful. Only 2"-3" tall, you can walk on it (releasing its lemony aroma), tuck it between pavers in a garden path, use it as a tidy border or fill in a flower bed. It grows quickly but isn't pushy, delivers texture, fragrance, and flowers, is great for cooking, and requires almost no care.
A hardy perennial in zones 4-9, Creeping Thyme has a place in almost every garden. It cascades nicely in a rockery, fills in cracks, spills out of planters. In summer, it's covered with tiny purple blooms that attract honeybees and butterflies. It can be planted as a lawn that never needs mowing.
Creeping Thyme thrives in full sun or light shade, well-draining soil, with occasional water. It blooms in late spring through early summer. The pink-purple blooms are so dense that they completely cover the foliage.  The rest of the year it's dense green. This is the most charming, versatile, and least demanding ground cover ever.
Surface sow the tiny seeds in a flat, keep them warm and moist, then tear off chunks of seedlings and plant them 6" apart.  They'll fill in over time.  This much seed will cover about 25 square feet.  Four packs will cover about 100 square feet. Sixteen packs will cover 1000 square feet, about a half a pound. 
1000 seeds

Product name: 100 pcs. of Freshly made incense sticks (choose five scents)
Description:
I am not going to tell you that my incense is the best on Etsy, least expensive on the web, or that it is second to none.
I will not tell you that my incense is doublely - triplely scented! nor will I say it will burn forever and the aroma will last longer than that.
I WILL SAY: sticks are standard 11 inches long. you will receive 100 pieces, broken down into 20 sticks per bag. I urge you to choose your five scents and list them in the comment/special instructions space provided when ordering. If you CAN NOT decide, simply type "SURPRISE ME" and that is what I will do. I will send five scents that I choose at random. 
Now, here are the fragrances I offer:
AMBER (white) -  A very elegant fragrance, addictive. A delicate and distinct musky scent of fresh amber. A surrounding aroma overall.
APPLE CIDER - The coziness of simmering cider is a seasonal classic.  A delightful blend of spices, sweet caramelized apples, cinnamon sticks, and the peel for a kick. 
ASIAN DREAM - Dream away to a mystical fantasy, an alluring forbidden forest.
ASPEN PINE -  Imagine yourself in a dense pine forest upon a snow covered mountain top.
 
AUTUMN SUNRISE - Deep earthy and cool, with hints of musk and spice. 
BLACKBERRY SAGE -  Freshly picked blackberries tempered with cool, crisp sage. A unique  and refreshing herbal balance 
 
BLACK COCONUT - Delicious! Vanilla, Tonka Bean, and a hint of White Florals bathed in coconut milk
BLACK MUSK - Deep, musky, dark, heavy, sensual in a mysterious way. 
BLUE GARDENIAS - A fresh, pretty, exotic floral arrangement.  
BUTT NAKED - Fresh green apples perfectly harmonized with refreshing melons and juicy pears.
CEDARWOOD - Cool, clean, and woodsy.
CHINA RAIN - Soft, subtle hints of lily of the valley, jasmine, hyacinth, rose, and ylang ylang.
CHESTNUT BROWN SUGAR - Toasted chestnuts drenched in a buttery brown sugar syrup. 
CINNAMON - A nip in the butt sort of sweet spice .... GOTCHA!
CITRONELLA - Crisp and refreshing without being overpowering. The clean and fresh lemony fragrance of citronella grass. BUGS B. GONE!
CITRUS BERRY - Tart, sweet, crisp, ....... a fruit basket free for all!
CLEAN COTTON - Picture putting on your favorite PJ's and snuggling under your warm, cozy blankie straight from the dryer.
CLOVE'S BLEND - Warm and spicy but not too overpowering.
COACH POPPY -  Cucumber, Mandarin, Freesia, Rose, Jasmine, Gardenia, Water lily, Sandalwood, Cedar, Vanilla and Marshmallow. Whatever it is, it's in there.
COMFORT ZONE -  Warmer that sunshine, stronger than moonshine, Could be yours - could be mine ... what's your comfort?
DOWN HOME COUNTRY - A cozy creation of fresh pine, balsam fir, mixed with warm spices, hot apple pie, and warm vanilla. 
DRAGON'S BLOOD - Autumn-like warm, woody and earthy scent, with notes of amber, vanilla, and sandalwood
 
EARTH - Vetiver, oak moss and patchouli blended with cool greens. A real scent of nature
EGYPTIAN MUSK - light, alluring, a scent of pure desire
EUCALYPTUS - An almost cool, minty woodsy brush (if there is such a thing) ... a real eye opener
FLIRTATIOUS - A youthful, delicate and feminine fragrance mix of florals with hints of plums and currants in a bed of light musk
FLOWER CHILD - A delicate blend of white florals innocently accented with the subtle sweetness of candy, layered in musk, sandalwood, and then patchouli 
FOREST ON THE MOUNTAIN - Rain showers fall upon leaves while giving fresh life to wild flowers in bloom. Fir, pine, balsam, and cedar wood trees stretch so high they touch the stars. Morning breaks with dew soaked grassland; while the air is fresher than the freedom you feel standing alone in this brisk, clean,  green paradise. 
FRANKINCENSE- Earthy. What else can I say?
GINGER COOKIE - Spicy and sweet gingerbread cookies - just like grandma made when you were a kid.
GOLDEN COFFEE -  Robust, freshly ground and brewed. The scent of eye-opening awareness in the morning.
HAWAIIAN PUNCH - The drink speaks for itself, fruity, sweet, powerful - a tropical classic.
HEAVENLY - A soft smooth and creamy fragrance blended with white peony and white musk.
HONEY -  A golden, warm, raw, unrefined buzzing sweetness.
HONEYDEW MELON - Delightful, sweet, and very fresh smelling. Very true to the original fruit.
INNER PEACE - Calming and relaxing. Lemon verbena, cypress and freshness with a hint of a woodsy feeling.
INTIMATE - A soothing blend of florals, soft woods, and Earthy undertones.
JAMAICAN ME CRAZY - Wow!  fruity, fresh and edgy with a  kick, an original secret blend of passion fruit, mangoes, citrus and SSHHH...a splash of cannabis
JASMINE - An ultra hip light, airy fragrance ... associated with the orient
LAVENDER - True to its name - Soft, pretty, simply lovely
LEMON DROPS - Mouth puckering sour lemon candies
LITTLE ANGELS - Innocence with a sparkling curiosity. Pink sugar, mild spices, orange whip, currants, pomegranate, cotton candy and creamy vanilla musk showcase all that truly is 'sugar and spice and everything nice'.
LOVERBOY - Sassy, delicate and modern. floral and musk.
MEDITATION - Deep eastern spices, patchouli and sandalwood sweetened with frankincense and grounded with light notes of nag champa and dragons blood. 
MIDNIGHT THERAPY - A soothing and relaxing blend of woods, musks, and earthy tones heightened with the aromatherapeutic scents of eucalyptus and spearmint. 
 MISTLETOE - Not the same boring old take on Christmas fragrance. Pine, Fir, Holly, and a hint of Santa's magic all year round.
MOUNTAIN AIR - A refreshing combination of woods, pines and a cool crisp breeze. 
MYSTERY MAJIK - Close your eyes and walk the paths of your thoughts to the shore of your dreams. See, perched high upon the foundation of peace ..... The threshold of your imagination.
NAG CHAMPA - Bold Earth.
OCEAN BREEZE - A Crisp ocean breeze that envelopes you as you walk along a secluded tropical beach, the waves gently spraying a fine mist that refreshes your soul and cleanses your mind. 
ORIENTAL GARDENIA - A blend of woods, plants, and flowers only found in the Eastern world.
PATCHOULI - Do you need to ask? A classic woodsy earth scent from the Far East.
PUMPKIN SPICE - Warm! Natural! and Robust!  Cinnamon, clove and nutmeg round out this hearty fall scent. (oh! ... and don't forget the pumpkin).
ROSE BED - A mixture of pink, red, yellow, and white roses. "A rose by any other name ..." - or is it?
ROYAL VANILLA - A true vanilla scent.
 
SAGE - Cool and crisp.
 
SANDALWOOD - Think bamboo.
SISTER MORPHINE - Clary sage, Cinnamon, Patchouli, Leather, and Sandalwood.
SOFT SPIRIT - Another scent that has been returned by request. Powdery, delicate lotus deepened with creamy vanilla sugar bound with sweet frankincense.
STRAWBERRY BANANA - Sweet Strawberry and delicious Banana blended perfectly together to make this mouth watering treat.
SUMMERTIME - A uniquely sweet, yet citrus blend of , honey, oranges, tangerines, papaya, and other tropical fruits highlighted with vanilla and coconut.
THUNDERBOLT -  Deep, dark, cool and mysterious with a heavy mood setter.
TWILIGHT TIME - A warm blanket of cashmere, amber, flowers (honeysuckle?); and that distinct, indescribable fragrance in the after midnight morning air. 
WALK IN THE WOODS - Dark, fresh, crisp and refreshing -- a brisk walk of nature 
 WINTER WONDERLAND - Take yourself a peaceful early morn' stroll  during a light snowfall in a quaint little town where silence is the only thing you hear.
**note: scents are subject to one's own interpretation.

Product name: Beatrix Potter Books Very Vintage, Vintage & Almost New
Description:
Beatrix Potter books are notoriously difficult to date. Here's what I found on the web:-
Reprints of Beatrix Potter's works usually resemble the original first editions in almost every detail, and can be hard to distinguish from them. The key points to look for are:
(a) the first editions are usually dated in the imprint at the foot of the title page, on the front (recto) of the leaf. The copyright date on the back (verso) will show the first date of publication, but this alone is not indicative of first edition status. Later printings have no date in the imprint.
(b) her publisher Frederick Warne became a limited company in 1917, after the great majority of her best-known books had been first published. Therefore, most books with "Limited" or "Ltd" in the company name, either in the imprint or on the front cover, are published in or after 1917 and are reprints.
(c) any edition bearing an ISBN (International Standard Book Number) was issued after 1967.
I have therefore separated my books into numbered categories:- 
1. Very Vintage, pre 1967 (no ISBN), 
2. Vintage (with ISBN) have pictures stuck to the front cover
3. Almost new have pictures printed onto the front cover
The prices are per book. As stock turns over the books pictured may no longer be available, please let me know if you would like photographs of the book/s you chose.
